{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 350°F. Line baking sheets with parchment and set aside.","Place flour, sugar, butter, egg and baking powder into mixing bowl and mix <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>.","Place some sugar on a plate. Take 1 tbsp dough and roll into a small ball (approx. 1¼ in.). Dip the top in sugar, place on prepared baking sheet and flatten with a fork into a round cookie shape. Repeat with remaining dough and bake for 20 minutes (350°F) or until lightly golden. Allow to cool on a wire rack before serving or storing in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["9 oz all-purpose flour","4 oz sugar, plus extra to dip cookies","4 oz unsalted butter, cold, cut into pieces","1 large egg","1 tsp baking powder"]}],"id":"r91154","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZYRBcBEBQ2Y\/XZWqK0A3klI\/AAAAAAAAfUI\/CtHdeiXlHkwA7XrJ5yrbinOQFmDMeooAQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_EyzR6Cokb66_J_lQ.png","title":"Butter Cookies","publishedAt":"2017-03-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"3 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"12 g","calories":"345 kJ \/ 82 kcal"},"usefulItems":"parchment paper, airtight container, baking sheets, wire rack, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Before mixing add natural flavors such as vanilla sugar, lemon zest, orange zest, ground cinnamon or chopped candied ginger and continue with recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","50m","30 pieces"]}